### 7.13 Role permissions payload rules

When creating or updating roles, the frontend should send permission names only.

```json
{
  "name": "Manager",
  "permissions": [
    "users.view",
    "users.create",
    "products.ai.menu"
  ]
}
```

Backend validation must ensure each permission exists:

```php
'permissions' => ['array'],
'permissions.*' => ['string', 'exists:permissions,name'],
```

Then sync permissions:

```php
$role->syncPermissions($data->permissions);
```

Do not let frontend send labels, modules, section labels, or descriptions when saving a role. Those values are backend-owned metadata.

Optional stricter validation using the catalog:

```php
use Illuminate\Validation\Rule;
use App\Support\Permissions\PermissionCatalog;

'permissions' => ['array'],
'permissions.*' => [
    'string',
    Rule::in(PermissionCatalog::names()),
],
```

Use `exists:permissions,name` when you want DB state to be the source of truth. Use `Rule::in(PermissionCatalog::names())` when enum catalog state is the source of truth.

